data.title: The Secret to a Happy Life — Lessons from 8 Decades of Research | Robert Waldinger | TED
data.description:
The happiest and healthiest people are those who have warm connections with others, says psychiatrist Robert Waldinger, who leads the Harvard Study of Adult Development -- one of the longest-running studies of adult life ever conducted. Exploring the crucial link between social bonds and quality of life, he shares wisdom and insights into how to identify and strengthen the relationships that impact your well-being most. When it comes to the people in your inner circle, "Turn toward the voices that make you feel more open and more inclusive," he says.

This conversation, hosted by TED current affairs curator Whitney Pennington Rodgers, was part of an exclusive TED Membership event. Visit http://www.ted.com/membership to become a TED Member.

Body Stuff with Dr. Jen Gunter, a TED series
data.subtitle: Think you know how your body works? Think again! Dr. Jen Gunter is here to shake up everything you thought you knew — from how much water you need to drink to how often you need to poop and everything in between. Join us weekly for this TED original series that will tell you the truth about what’s *really* going on inside you. Want to hear more from Dr. Jen Gunter? Check out her podcast Body Stuff from the TED Audio Collective.
